benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/allTags - Retrieve account tags

covered: Valid Request scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC17, TC18, TC19, TC21, TC27)
Query Parameters coverage (TC02, TC03, TC12, TC13, TC21, TC22)
Error handling and status codes coverage (TC08, TC11, TC12, TC15, TC27)
Concurrency and integration scenarios (TC23, TC18, TC19, TC24)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested (no explicit pagination parameters/test for paging or per-page limits)
Rate limiting / throttling behavior is not tested (multiple requests in short time)
Caching behavior verification is not tested (ETag/Cache-Control headers or caching implications)
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests (e.g., page size, page number, total pages, and proper handling when there are more than a page worth of tags)
Add rate limiting tests to ensure proper throttling and error handling under high request load
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control presence and correct validation of cached responses
Consider explicit 401/403 edge cases beyond TC10 for broader authorization coverage
Include a focused test to confirm behavior when query parameters are partially provided or malformed (beyond what TC22 covers)
